                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17170111-3-off14 t17170111-3-cd12"></join> last. The Prosecutor's Servant depos'd that Mary Pearse came in to buy a pair of Shoes, but not agreeing for the Price, went away; upon which he missing the Shoes, follow'd her, and seeing her go into a Toy-shop with Sarah Cook, went in and charged them with the Shoes, and a Constable being sent for, Sarah Cook dropp'd the Shoes in the Shop. The Prisoners deny'd the Fact; but the Evidence being positive, the Jury found them both <rs id="t17170111-3-verdict13" type="verdictDescription">
